  "text": "where g µν is an AAdS 5 metric that has ∂ V as a Killing vector. As shown in appendix A the isometries of the TsT transformed metricḡ µν are precisely all the AAdS 5 Killing vectors that commute with the AAdS 5 Killing vector ∂ V . The class of ASch 5 space-times that we will focus on are all space-times that result from applying TsT to those pure AAdS 5 space-times that admit a Killing vector N = ∂ V that asymptotically commutes with the Schrödinger algebra, so that N is asymptotically null. This follows from the fact that the embedding of the Schrödinger algebra into the AdS isometry algebra is essentially unique [CITATION_1] and that this embedding is such that the Schrödinger algebra consists of all those AdS 5 isometries that commute with a null Killing vector.",
